  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Rinse fish fillets and pat dry with paper towels.",
    "In a small bowl, mix minced garlic and lemon juice.",
    "In a large bowl, combine rice, chicken broth, salt, and black pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer.",
    "Thread fish, garlic-lemon mixture, and parsley onto bamboo skewers.",
    "Brush olive oil onto the bottom of a baking dish or bamboo tray.",
    "Arrange skewers onto the prepared baking dish and roast for 25 minutes.",
    "Stir cooked rice mixture and top with roasted fish and garlic-lemon mixture.",
    "Return to oven and roast for an additional 10 minutes.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
